---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Features from '~/components/widgets/Features.astro';
import Stats from '~/components/widgets/Stats.astro';
import CallToAction from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Meridian — The First Real-Time Psychological Stability Index for Active Traders',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
};

const marqueeRow1 = [
  {
    quote: "Three months in. I thought I had clean execution — the overtrading metric disagreed from day one.",
    name: 'Jason K.',
    role: 'Futures day trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "Passed my third Apex evaluation. The first two I blew up on days where, in hindsight, I should have just closed the platform. The pattern was obvious once I could see it.",
    name: 'Mike R.',
    role: 'Prop firm trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "Turned out I wasn't losing because of my entries. I was adding to losing positions and ignoring my own rules. Took data to admit it.",
    name: 'Anonymous',
    role: '',
  },
  {
    quote: "I don't use tools that send my fill data to the cloud. Local-only was non-negotiable for me.",
    name: 'David Chen',
    role: 'Independent trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "It doesn't close your positions for you — that part is still on you. But I stopped pretending I didn't notice the score dropping while I was moving my stop around.",
    name: 'T. Rodriguez',
    role: 'NQ futures',
  },
  {
    quote: "The seven bars make it immediately clear which habit is pulling the score down. I kept telling myself I was trading fine. The data disagreed consistently.",
    name: 'Elena V.',
    role: 'MNQ scalper',
  },
  {
    quote: "Being able to use Market Replay without it touching my live baseline was more useful than I expected.",
    name: 'Chris P.',
    role: 'Futures swing',
  },
  {
    quote: "I run two accounts with copy fills. I was expecting double-counting issues in the score. It handled it cleanly without any configuration.",
    name: 'Jordan L.',
    role: 'Multi-account',
  },
  {
    quote: "After a losing session I used to review charts to explain what happened. Now I check the session report first. It's faster and more honest.",
    name: 'Sam W.',
    role: 'ES / NQ',
  },
  {
    quote: "Didn't want another subscription. Tried the trial anyway. Kept it — the overlay is actually readable mid-session without being in the way.",
    name: 'Rina M.',
    role: 'Day trader',
  },
];

const marqueeRow2 = [
  {
    quote: "The caution signal fired and I decided I could manage through it. Twenty minutes later I had hit my daily limit. I can't blame the tool — I ignored it.",
    name: 'Sara',
    role: 'ES trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "I've restarted funded accounts more times than I want to count. If someone had told me a revenge-entry detector would matter more than another indicator, I wouldn't have believed them.",
    name: 'Alex Nowak',
    role: 'Prop trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "Four years trading NQ. Thought I had a solid read on my own behavior. First week of data showed me I had several habits I wasn't aware of.",
    name: 'James O.',
    role: 'Day trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "Post-session journals have their place. This is different — the feedback arrives while the session is still running, not the next morning.",
    name: 'Anonymous',
    role: '',
  },
  {
    quote: "Took a few sessions to calibrate. Once it did, the alerts started making sense — I could trace each one back to a specific pattern.",
    name: 'Priya S.',
    role: 'Futures trader',
  },
  {
    quote: "The stop-widening flag caught me doing something I always denied — moving my stop out when a trade went against me. Useful confirmation, even if it wasn't comfortable.",
    name: 'Marcus T.',
    role: 'CL / GC',
  },
  {
    quote: "Thought my exits were disciplined. Turns out there's a consistent pattern on certain days. I don't love it, but I can work with the information.",
    name: 'Kim H.',
    role: 'Index futures',
  },
  {
    quote: "A rough Tuesday doesn't disappear from the score just because Wednesday started. That's accurate. That's how it actually feels.",
    name: 'Leo B.',
    role: 'Overnight + day',
  },
  {
    quote: "The alerts are infrequent enough that I don't tune them out. When one fires, I actually pause before doing anything.",
    name: 'Andre C.',
    role: 'Prop + personal',
  },
  {
    quote: "The history view is simple. I like that. Seeing consistent streaks makes discipline feel measurable instead of just a goal.",
    name: 'Nina F.',
    role: 'Futures',
  },
];
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <Hero
    actions={[
      {
        variant: 'primary',
        text: 'Start free trial — 7 days',
        href: 'https://meridianpsi.lemonsqueezy.com/checkout/buy/b7b8b514-fefa-4a34-8cad-d2e68f564d25',
        icon: 'tabler:player-play',
      },
      { text: 'See pricing', href: '/pricing' },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title">
      Every trader has a plan.
      <br />
      <span class="text-accent dark:text-emerald-700">The market's job is to make you forget it.</span>
    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <strong>Meridian</strong> is the first real-time psychological stability index for active traders. It tracks seven behavioral dimensions, builds and updates dynamic statistical baselines from your own session history and performance, and combines behavioral-finance and cognitive-science models with rigorous on-device mathematics to compute your PSI score — entirely on your PC, with no cloud uploads.
      <br /><br />
      It tracks seven behavioral dimensions during your live session. Each dimension is scored on-device using statistical modeling — personalized baselines, asymmetric EWMA-style pressure dynamics, and patterns grounded in behavioral finance and trading psychology (informed by years of live futures experience) — then combined into one PSI score so you can see rising behavioral pressure before the next trade.
      <br /><br />
      <span class="text-zinc-500 font-normal">Most psychology tools analyze what happened. Meridian tells you what's happening — <em>right now</em>.</span>
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <Stats
    stats={[
      { title: 'Behavioral dimensions tracked', amount: '7' },
      { title: 'PSI update after every fill', amount: '<100ms' },
      { title: 'Free trial', amount: '7 days' },
      { title: 'Per month after trial', amount: '$24.99' },
    ]}
  />

  <!-- Problem recognition section -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-zinc-50/60">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">
        You know what you should have done.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-zinc-600 mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Every trader walks away from a bad session knowing exactly where it went wrong.
        The problem isn't knowledge — it's that in the middle of a live session, you can't see yourself clearly.
      </p>
      <ul class="text-left max-w-lg mx-auto space-y-4 mb-12">
        {[
          'Added size right after a loss',
          'Moved the stop to "give it a little more room"',
          'Took the next trade too fast — still feeling the last one',
          'Held a loser longer than your plan ever allowed',
          'Broke your session rule — just this once',
          'Hit your daily limit and took one more anyway',
        ].map((item) => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-base text-zinc-700">
            <span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-red-400 shrink-0"></span>
            {item}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-900 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Meridian doesn't tell you what to trade.<br />
        It tells you <em>where you are</em> — so you can decide whether to continue.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Features
    id="features"
    tagline="How it works"
    title="Not a journal. Not a mood tracker. A precision instrument."
    subtitle="Meridian applies a multi-dimensional behavioral model — drawing from trading psychology, cognitive science, and behavioral finance — to produce a single, mathematically rigorous score in real time."
    items={[
      {
        title: 'A composite behavioral index — updated in under 100ms',
        description:
          'After every fill, Meridian recalculates PSI across all seven dimensions simultaneously — no artificial delay. The score reflects behavioral pressure inferred from your session activity (executions, holds, and rule compliance), so you get feedback before the next decision.',
        icon: 'tabler:gauge',
      },
      {
        title: 'Seven dimensions drawn from behavioral and cognitive research',
        description:
          'Revenge Entry · Stop Manipulation · Size Spike · Rushed Exit · Position Overstay · Rule Violations · Overtrading Pace — each dimension targets a distinct cognitive failure mode documented in trading psychology and behavioral finance literature. They run independently and compound into a single score.',
        icon: 'tabler:brain',
      },
      {
        title: 'Personalized statistical baseline — not a generic threshold',
        description:
          'Meridian builds a statistical model of your specific trading behavior using Welford online estimation — tracking your historical hold times, position sizes, and entry pace. The score is calibrated against your own history, not an industry average. It converges meaningfully around 30 sessions.',
        icon: 'tabler:chart-dots',
      },
      {
        title: 'EWMA-weighted scoring with asymmetric pressure dynamics',
        description:
          'Behavioral pressure accumulates fast and recovers slowly — mirroring how cognitive load actually works under stress. Each dimension uses exponential weighted decay, so a single bad decision doesn\'t define you, but a pattern absolutely does.',
        icon: 'tabler:math-function',
      },
      {
        title: 'Overnight carry: psychological debt doesn\'t reset overnight',
        description:
          'Unresolved behavioral pressure carries forward between sessions with a time-decay model. A bad Tuesday doesn\'t vanish from your score Wednesday morning. Markets rest — stress responses don\'t.',
        icon: 'tabler:moon',
      },
      {
        title: 'Completely local. Zero network calls. Ever.',
        description:
          'No accounts, no cloud sync, no telemetry. Your fills, session history, and behavioral baseline never leave your machine. Meridian runs entirely inside NinjaTrader 8 — a native add-on, not a connected service.',
        icon: 'tabler:cloud-off',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <!-- Testimonials — dual-row infinite marquee -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-zinc-50 border-t border-zinc-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-emerald-700 uppercase mb-2">What traders say</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-900">From traders who've been there</h2>
    </div>

    <div
      class="overflow-hidden"
      style="mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black 12%, black 88%, transparent); -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, black 12%, black 88%, transparent);"
    >
      <!-- Row 1: scroll left — two strips, no gap between strips, so -50% == one full cycle -->
      <div class="marquee-left flex w-max mb-3 will-change-transform">
        <div class="flex gap-3 shrink-0">
          {marqueeRow1.map((t) => (
            <div class="w-60 shrink-0 bg-white rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 px-4 py-3.5 shadow-sm">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 mb-2">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 select-none">
                    {t.name === 'Anonymous' ? '?' : t.name.charAt(0)}
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 text-xs leading-tight">{t.name}</p>
                    {t.role && <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">{t.role}</p>}
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-0.5 shrink-0">
                  {Array(5).fill(null).map(() => (
                    <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                      <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
                    </svg>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-zinc-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">"{t.quote}"</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
          {marqueeRow1.map((t) => (
            <div class="w-60 shrink-0 bg-white rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 px-4 py-3.5 shadow-sm">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 mb-2">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 select-none">
                    {t.name === 'Anonymous' ? '?' : t.name.charAt(0)}
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 text-xs leading-tight">{t.name}</p>
                    {t.role && <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">{t.role}</p>}
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-0.5 shrink-0">
                  {Array(5).fill(null).map(() => (
                    <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                      <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
                    </svg>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-zinc-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">"{t.quote}"</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Row 2: scroll right -->
      <div class="marquee-right flex w-max will-change-transform">
        <div class="flex gap-3 shrink-0">
          {marqueeRow2.map((t) => (
            <div class="w-60 shrink-0 bg-white rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 px-4 py-3.5 shadow-sm">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 mb-2">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 select-none">
                    {t.name === 'Anonymous' ? '?' : t.name.charAt(0)}
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 text-xs leading-tight">{t.name}</p>
                    {t.role && <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">{t.role}</p>}
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-0.5 shrink-0">
                  {Array(5).fill(null).map(() => (
                    <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                      <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
                    </svg>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-zinc-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">"{t.quote}"</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
          {marqueeRow2.map((t) => (
            <div class="w-60 shrink-0 bg-white rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 px-4 py-3.5 shadow-sm">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2 mb-2">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 select-none">
                    {t.name === 'Anonymous' ? '?' : t.name.charAt(0)}
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 text-xs leading-tight">{t.name}</p>
                    {t.role && <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">{t.role}</p>}
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-0.5 shrink-0">
                  {Array(5).fill(null).map(() => (
                    <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                      <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
                    </svg>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-zinc-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">"{t.quote}"</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-xs text-zinc-400 mt-6 italic">Results may vary. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder note -->
  <section class="py-14 px-6 bg-white border-t border-zinc-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex gap-6 items-start">
      <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center select-none">G</div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-zinc-700 leading-relaxed text-base italic">
          "I built Meridian because I kept blowing up sessions that had no reason to go wrong. The strategy was solid. The market wasn't the problem. I was. I needed something that told me that <em>while it was happening</em> — not the next morning in a journal."
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-400 font-medium">— Gary Caffrey, Founder of Meridian &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="/about" class="underline hover:text-zinc-600">Read the full story →</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-10 px-6 bg-zinc-50/80 border-t border-zinc-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed text-center">
        PSI is a behavioral proxy index derived from your trading activity inside NinjaTrader. It does not measure physiology (for example heart rate or stress hormones), and it is not validated as a predictor of trading profits or losses. Meridian is designed to improve self-awareness and discipline during a session; outcomes still depend on many factors beyond psychology.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CallToAction
    actions={[
      {
        variant: 'primary',
        text: 'Start free trial — 7 days',
        href: 'https://meridianpsi.lemonsqueezy.com/checkout/buy/b7b8b514-fefa-4a34-8cad-d2e68f564d25',
        icon: 'tabler:player-play',
      },
      {
        text: 'See pricing',
        href: '/pricing',
      },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title">Every session starts with the best intentions.</Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      Meridian helps you keep them.
      <br />
      <span class="text-sm text-muted italic mt-2 block">
        $24.99/month after 7-day trial · cancel any time · NinjaTrader 8 required.
        Trading involves substantial risk of loss. Meridian does not guarantee trading results.
      </span>
    </Fragment>
  </CallToAction>
</Layout>

<style>
  .marquee-left {
    animation: marquee-left 130s linear infinite;
  }
  .marquee-right {
    animation: marquee-right 130s linear infinite;
  }
  @keyframes marquee-left {
    from { transform: translateX(0); }
    to   { transform: translateX(-50%); }
  }
  @keyframes marquee-right {
    from { transform: translateX(-50%); }
    to   { transform: translateX(0); }
  }
  .marquee-left:hover,
  .marquee-right:hover {
    animation-play-state: paused;
  }
</style>
